The paper deals with a problem related to social networks and voting systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. The use of probability distributions and the study of approximation algorithms suggest that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The problem of election control is related to game theory, which could place the paper in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category. The use of influence and diffusion models suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the study of approximation algorithms and hardness results could place the paper in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
